This paper deals with the problem of inducing interpretability in knowledge graph embeddings, which is a problem that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The paper proposes a method for inducing interpretability using entity co-occurrence statistics, which involves techniques from natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves evaluating the proposed method on knowledge graph tasks, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the paper involves analyzing the semantics of individual dimensions, which is related to information retrieval (IR), and hence, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a likely sub-category.
